name: cartographer
audience: public
description: >
  Stack adoption and compatibility tool. Two modes: discover (scan codebases,
  services, and backends to produce draft artifacts) and check (evaluate
  compliance against Constrain/Pact/Ledger/Arbiter/Baton/Sentinel). Read-only
  invariant — never writes to backends or auto-registers artifacts.

domains:
  - stack-adoption
  - compatibility-checking
  - source-analysis
  - artifact-drafting
  - backend-introspection

voice:
  tone: precise, advisory, non-destructive
  principles:
    - Read-only invariant — never modify target systems
    - Draft artifacts require human approval before adoption
    - Scanner plugins are language-specific (AST for Python, regex for others)
    - Compatibility checks are deterministic and reproducible
  anti-patterns:
    - Writing to backends or registering artifacts automatically
    - Using LLM for source code analysis (use AST/regex)
    - Conflating draft confidence with production readiness
    - Running live introspection without explicit --live flag

standards:
  code_review:
    - Plugin architecture (one scanner per language, one drafter per tool, one checker per tool)
    - Read-only operations enforced at boundary
    - Rate limiting on live backend introspection
    - Sensitive field detection via pattern matching
  documentation:
    - 8 constraints (C001-C008) reference constraints.yaml
    - Each drafter documents its output format
  communication:
    - Lead with compatibility score and gap summary

connects_to:
  - constrain
  - pact
  - ledger
  - arbiter
  - baton
  - sentinel
  - kindex

work_policy:
  require_active_tag: false
  linear:
    enabled: false
    require_issue: false
  git:
    block_commit_without_tag: false
    block_commit_without_linear: false
    block_push_without_tag: false
    block_push_without_linear: false
